        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A–2 Let C1 and C2 be circles whose centers are 10 units apart, and whose radi are 1 and 3. Find, with proof, the locus of all points M for which there exists points X on C1 and Y on C2 such that M is the midpoint of the line segment XY.",
